# CPM weekly status workflow

Canonical repo: `https://github.com/solzito148/cpm`  
Work directory: `weekly/`

## When this applies

Any update to the weekly status deck, including:

- `CPM-ProcurementForecasting-Status.xlsx`
- `generate_cashflow_status_pptx.py`
- `assets/aes-logo.png`
- Generated deck (written to `/Users/msanes/Cursor/aes/cashflow/weekly/CASHFLOW_Status_*.pptx`, not under `cpm/weekly/`)

## Required steps after changes

1. If Excel or generator changed, regenerate:
   ```bash
   cd weekly && python3 generate_cashflow_status_pptx.py
   ```
2. Source data stays in `cpm/weekly/`; the `.pptx` is always saved under `/Users/msanes/Cursor/aes/cashflow/weekly/`.
3. **Always commit** relevant changes to `main` when the weekly status task is complete (user expects this without asking again).
4. Push to `origin main` as `solzito148` (see `github-account` rule).

## Commit message

One short sentence focused on **why** (e.g. "Update weekly status deck for May 29 with paginated tables and AES logo").

Include: `.xlsx` source, generator script, and logo asset. Do not commit generated `.pptx` (output lives under `aes/cashflow/weekly/`). Do not commit secrets.

## Deck conventions

- Tables: max **10 rows per slide**, title suffix `(page/total)` when paginated.
- AES logo on **first** and **last** slide (`assets/aes-logo.png`).
- Report date: edit `report_date` in `generate_cashflow_status_pptx.py` → `main()`.
